Horizon Bank's headquarters is shown in downtown Michigan City. Horizon Bank President and Chief Credit Officer Thomas H. Edwards is retiring. 


Joseph S. Pete, The Times































































editor's pick urgent


        
        Horizon Bank executive Thomas H. Edward to retire
    


Joseph S. Pete
joseph.pete@nwi.com, 219-933-3316











Joseph S Pete

































            Jul 19, 2017
        Updated Jul 19, 2017













































Buy Now


Horizon Bank's headquarters is shown in downtown Michigan City. Horizon Bank President and Chief Credit Officer Thomas H. Edwards is retiring.


Joseph S. Pete, The Times



















































Horizon Bank President and Chief Credit Officer Thomas H. Edward plans to retire.“Mr. Edwards has provided leadership, guidance and inspiration throughout his years with Horizon, generously giving of his time and expertise to the company and the community,” said Horizon Bancorp Chairman and CEO Craig M. Dwight.
“As president and chief credit officer, he presided over a period of unprecedented growth and successfully guided Horizon through the great recession. We wish to thank Mr. Edwards for his years of service and to wish him the best in his retirement years.”Edward has been the Michigan City-based bank's president and chief credit officer since 2002, responsible for commercial credit underwriting, allowance for loan and lease loss reserves, treasury management and wealth and investment management.

His replacement will be Dennis J. Kuhn, who will step into the role in October after a transition period.Kuhn, who started his banking career in Michigan in 1985, helped Horizon launch its branch in Kalamazoo in May 2010. He had previously worked as a commercial loan officer for First of America Bank in LaPorte and been president and CEO of Portage Commerce Bank in Michigan.“Horizon is fortunate to have a person of Mr. Kuhn’s caliber, who is well known to us and has a shared credit philosophy," Dwight said. "In addition, Mr. Edwards retirement date at year-end provides for a seamless transition.”









