Our Team









Expert credentials.  Tremendous experience.  Valuable tenure.  Our Big 4 and industry work experience, combined with extensive executive search expertise, gives us insight into the most technical details of our clients’ needs. Our candidates and clients know their search is in qualified hands.  


Meet our award-winning team of professionals:

 
 
Cliff T. Edwards, MBA  - President, CEO and Majority Owner
Email: cliff@thomasedwards.com


Connect: 



Cliff is the CEO and majority shareholder of Thomas, Edwards Group. Prior to starting Thomas, Edwards Group, Cliff held various financial roles in banking, accounting and management consulting. He was a Manager in Coopers & Lybrand's national banking and real estate consulting groups. Before that, he was a commercial real estate lender at a regional savings bank, an accounting manager for a financial institution and a staff auditor in public accounting. He earned a BBA in Accounting from the University of Oklahoma. He also earned an MBA in Finance from the Wharton School of Business. Cliff passed the CPA exam in 1985 but is no longer licensed to practice. Cliff is a Board member of the Dallas Chapter of Financial Executives International (FEI). 

Under Cliff’s vision and leadership, Thomas, Edwards Group made the Inc. 5000 list in 2016, has won "Best Places to Work" awards several times and is regularly included in the Dallas Business Journal's Book of Lists.  The company celebrated its 20th year in business in February 2017.
 

 
 
Sharon Lukich, CPA - Partner, Director of Business Development
Email: sharon@thomasedwards.com


Connect: 



Sharon has over 10 years of experience in accounting and management consulting. Prior to entering the search industry, she served as Controller for a major division of the Baylor Health Care System. Sharon started her career in the Big 4 with PricewaterhouseCoopers (formerly Coopers & Lybrand), specializing in both audit and litigation consulting. She has been with Thomas, Edwards Group since 2001. In addition to being a Partner with the firm, Sharon also directs the firm’s Business Development efforts.  For the first 14 years with the firm, she was a Senior Search Consultant in the Executive Search Division. She earned a BS in Accounting Control Systems from the University of North Texas and is a licensed CPA in the state of Texas. Sharon serves on the board of the TSCPA and is a former DCPAS board member. She is a multi-year Professional Search award winner for both the Dallas and Texas areas. 

Sharon is married with two children.  In addition to her participation in various professional organizations, Sharon is very active in the fight to raise awareness and end autism.


 
 
Tom Delanoy, CPA - Partner, Managing Director
Email: tom@thomasedwards.com


Connect: 



Tom has more than a dozen years of experience in progressive accounting and finance functions across the manufacturing, hospitality and service industries. He served as Director of Planning and Analysis for the international division of Yum! Brands. Tom also was Controller for Brach’s Confections, and began his career in Big 4 audit with PricewaterhouseCoopers (formerly Price Waterhouse). He has been with Thomas, Edwards Group since 2006, having worked in both the Executive Search and the Contract Services Divisions. After 3 years with the firm, Tom was promoted into the role of Managing Director. Tom is a proud Aggie. He earned a BBA in Accounting from Texas A&M University and is a licensed CPA in the state of Texas. He is a multi-year Professional Search award winner for the Contract Services category in Dallas. During Tom’s tenure as Managing Director, Thomas, Edwards Group was named to the Inc. 5000 list.

Tom is married and has three children.  He has been active in youth sports, including coaching as well as serving in leadership roles.

 
 
 
Debbie Vanicek, CPA - Director, Executive Search Division 
Email: debbie@thomasedwards.com


Connect: 



Debbie has 16 years of corporate and operational accounting experience, including financial reporting, process re-engineering and software implementations. She started her career in Big 4 audit with Ernst & Young (formerly Arthur Young) before moving into industry. Debbie served as Controller for a hi-tech company, and was in a management role with Frito-Lay. She also was Assistant Controller for Weblink Wireless (formerly PageMart Wireless). Debbie has been with Thomas, Edwards Group since 2004, having worked in the Contract Services division prior to moving into the Executive Search Division where she currently serves as Director of that group. She earned her BBA in Accounting from Texas Tech University and is a licensed CPA in the state of Texas. Debbie is a multi-year Professional Search award winner for the Dallas and Texas areas. 

Debbie is a previous board member and remains very active with the Institute of Management Accountants (IMA).

 
 
Monica Westerfield, MBA - Candidate Recruiter
 Email: monica@thomasedwards.com


Connect: 



Monica began her career in internal audit with NationsBank, focusing on internal controls documentation as well as financial and operational audits for the Trust, Mortgage, and General Bank areas. Prior to joining the Thomas, Edwards’ team in 2010, she was a Staffing Manager in both agency and corporate recruiting roles with additional experience in on-site staffing for a high-profile client and experience in out-placement assistance with a well-respected branch of a global career services organization.   Monica specializes in finding talent in the areas of accounting, finance, and human resources at all levels and across multiple industries.  Additionally, she works with the TEG management team to provide training to new employees of the firm.  Monica earned both an MBA and a BS in Accounting from Oklahoma State University.

Monica is an active volunteer in her sons’ school and sports organizations. She has also served on and/or chaired several committees at Grace Avenue UMC that revolve around finance, human resources, and welcoming new members and currently is on the Staff-Parish Relations Committee.  Monica has also served as a past hospitality chairman of the Pi Beta Phi alumnae chapter for the Richardson-Plano area.  
 


  
 
Ben Pinto, CPA - Director, Contract Services Division
 Email: ben@thomasedwards.com



Connect: 



Ben brings 20+ years of accounting and finance experience working with companies of various sizes and industries including insurance, manufacturing, oil & gas, professional services, real estate and retail. He currently serves as Director of the Contract Services Division for the firm.  Prior to joining Thomas, Edwards Group, Ben was a Business Development Manager and an Executive Search Recruiter with a professional services firm for 12 years. He also served as a Regional Manager and VP for a national, privately-held company in the automotive industry. He began his career in Big 4 audit with Ernst & Young and is a Texas CPA and member of the Dallas Chapter of CPAs. A proud Aggie, Ben graduated from Texas A&M University with a BBA in Accounting. 

Ben is married to his college sweetheart and has two grown daughters and a son-in-law (also all Aggies-whoop!). He is a longtime member of Watermark Community Church and serves with several not for profit organizations including Water is Basic, The Marcella Project and New Friends New Life.



 
 
Sara Janicula - Senior Staffing Consultant
 Email: sara@thomasedwards.com


Connect: 



Sara is a graduate of the University of Oregon where she earned a BS in Business Administration. She also studied in Alaska, Illinois and Tennessee before becoming an Oregon Duck. Sara graduated Summa Cum Laude and worked full time while attending school. She began her professional career with Thomas, Edwards Group after graduation. She started with the Executive Search Division in 2012 and is currently working in the Contract Services Division. 

Sara enjoys mountain biking, beach volleyball, the symphony, and spending time with her family including her husband and identical twin sister.



  
 
Mindy Morse - Search Consultant
Email: mindy@thomasedwards.com


Connect: 



Mindy brings 8 years of finance experience across the insurance, investments and non-profit industries. Before joining the Executive Search Division of Thomas, Edwards Group in 2014, she served as Financial Analyst & Grants Manager for Dallas CASA. Prior to CASA, Mindy worked with AXA Advisors and the United Bank of Switzerland. She held the Series 7, 66 and Group 1 licenses while consulting with clients on their investment and insurance portfolio strategy. Mindy earned a BBA in Finance from the University of Texas at Austin where she was active in the Pi Beta Phi sorority and the UT Waterski Team. 

Mindy competes in half marathons and enjoys yoga. She is a member of Watermark Community Church where she serves in leadership within the single’s ministry.

  
 
Kristy Kim – Search Consultant
Email: kristy@thomasedwards.com


Connect: 



Kristy has several years of finance experience in the insurance industry, including client side consulting across a variety of industries for non-profits, small and midsize businesses and also national clients. Before joining the Executive Search Division of Thomas, Edwards Group in 2015, she served as a Risk Consultant for Liberty Mutual Holdings and previously was a Business Analyst performing variance analysis and delivering continuous improvement initiatives with LEAN methodologies. Kristy earned a BBA in Finance from the University of Texas at Austin where she was active in the Delta Sigma Pi business fraternity, Forever Texas spirit group, and a founding member of the BBA Women’s Forum. She also holds the Associate in Risk Management (ARM) designation. Kristy is currently a board member of 4Word, a national professional women’s organization. 

When she is not traveling with her husband and son Kristy enjoys training for marathons but would much rather be trail running. She is a member of Watermark Community Church where she actively serves in the Careers in Motion ministry dedicated to helping job seekers during periods of transition and career change.

 
 
Lance Friedensohn – Senior Staffing Consultant
Email: lance@thomasedwards.com


Connect: 



